<subSubSection id="89A6C9CBFFDCBA1CFFACF9D0FBC2FF44" pageId="61" pageNumber="952" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C1039A40FFDCBA1CFFACF9D0FE35F80A" blockId="61.[113,754,1635,1980]" pageId="61" pageNumber="952">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFDCBA1CFFACF9D0FF6CF9CA" bold="true" box="[113,225,1635,1659]" pageId="61" pageNumber="952">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Carapace squarish; epibranchial tooth absent, lateral margin entire; posterolateral margins gently converging towards posterior carapace margin; outer surface of chela gently convex, covered with large rounded granules in adults, ventral margin of palm sinuous, unarmed; male pleon triangular, appears more elongate; suture between male thoracic sternites 3 and 4 distinct; male sternopleonal cavity with press-button of pleonal locking mechanism on sternite 5; distal part of G1 gently swollen with main chitinous part forming beak-like structure and smaller projection basally. In life, chelae beige to cream.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C1039A40FFDCBA1CFFACF850FBC2FF44" blockId="61.[113,752,2019,2076]" lastBlockId="61.[813,1452,189,245]" pageId="61" pageNumber="952">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFDCBA1CFFACF850FF4EF84A" bold="true" box="[113,195,2019,2043]" pageId="61" pageNumber="952">Colour</emphasis>
. In life, the carapace and appendages are cream to buff, with the dorsal surface of the carapace possessing darker blotches (
<figureCitation id="598786C5FFDCBA1CFC3CFF0EFBC9FF64" box="[993,1092,189,213]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="88.[136,171,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[136,1474,324,1860]" captionTargetId="figure-7@88.[136,1474,324,1860]" captionTargetPageId="88" captionText="Fig. 56. Colour in life. A, B, Pseudosesarma edwardsii, male (20.5 × 19.3 mm) (ZRC 2016.0608), Langkawi [photograph: Paul Ng]; C–E, P. edwardsii, male (19.4 × 18.2 mm) (SMF), Langkawi, Peninsular Malaysia [photograph: CD Schubart]; F, G, P. crassimanum, (12.6 × 10.5 mm) (ZRC 2010.0035), Tioman, Peninsular Malaysia [photograph: PKL Ng]; H, P. boulengeri, specimen not preserved [photograph: Reza Naderloo]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5351399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5351399/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="952">Fig. 56H</figureCitation>
) (see also 
<bibRefCitation id="A52DE7B1FFDCBA1CFB64FF0EFAF0FF64" author="Naderloo" box="[1209,1405,189,213]" firstAuthor="Naderloo" page="7" pageId="61" pageNumber="952" pagination="1 - 43" refId="ref73052" refString="Naderloo R (2011) Grapsoid crabs (Decapoda: Brachyura: Thoracotremata) of the Persian Gulf and the Gulf of Oman. Zootaxa, 3048: 1 - 43." type="journal article" year="2011">Naderloo, 2011: 7</bibRefCitation>
a, b; 
<bibRefCitation id="A52DE7B1FFDCBA1CFCF0FF6EFC55FF44" author="Naderloo" box="[813,984,221,245]" firstAuthor="Naderloo" pageId="61" pageNumber="952" refId="ref73084" refString="Naderloo R (2017) Atlas of crabs of the Persian Gulf. Springer, 440 pp." type="book" year="2017">Naderloo, 2017</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 31.1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="89A6C9CBFFDCBA1CFCF0FEAEFB57FEE4" pageId="61" pageNumber="952" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C1039A40FFDCBA1CFCF0FEAEFB57FEE4" blockId="61.[813,1451,285,341]" pageId="61" pageNumber="952">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFDCBA1CFCF0FEAEFC18FE84" bold="true" box="[813,917,285,309]" pageId="61" pageNumber="952">Remarks</emphasis>
. The taxonomy of this species has been treated at length by 
<bibRefCitation id="A52DE7B1FFDCBA1CFC46FE8EFB5AFEE4" author="Naderloo &amp; Schubart" box="[923,1239,317,341]" firstAuthor="Naderloo" pageId="61" pageNumber="952" pagination="61 - 68" refId="ref73102" refString="Naderloo R &amp; Schubart CD (2009) Redescription and mitochondrial identification of Chiromantes boulengeri (Calman, 1920) (Decapoda: Brachyura: Sesarmidae) based on fresh material from the Persian Gulf, Iran. Zootaxa, 2128: 61 - 68." type="journal article" year="2009">Naderloo &amp; Schubart (2009)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="89A6C9CBFFDCBA1CFCF0FECEFBDBFDA4" pageId="61" pageNumber="952" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="C1039A40FFDCBA1CFCF0FECEFBDBFDA4" blockId="61.[813,1452,381,533]" pageId="61" pageNumber="952">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFDCBA1CFCF0FECEFC0BFE24" bold="true" box="[813,902,381,405]" pageId="61" pageNumber="952">Biology</emphasis>
. In 
<collectingCountry id="B9ABDAD0FFDCBA1CFC64FECDFC65FE24" box="[953,1000,382,405]" name="Iran" pageId="61" pageNumber="952">Iran</collectingCountry>
, the species lives in burrows along the muddy banks of rivers subject to tidal influence (
<bibRefCitation id="A52DE7B1FFDCBA1CFA9AFE2EFB8CFE64" author="Naderloo &amp; Schubart" firstAuthor="Naderloo" pageId="61" pageNumber="952" pagination="61 - 68" refId="ref73102" refString="Naderloo R &amp; Schubart CD (2009) Redescription and mitochondrial identification of Chiromantes boulengeri (Calman, 1920) (Decapoda: Brachyura: Sesarmidae) based on fresh material from the Persian Gulf, Iran. Zootaxa, 2128: 61 - 68." type="journal article" year="2009">Naderloo &amp; Schubart, 2009</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus id="1E0724E2FFDCBA1CFB92FE0DFBF2FE67" box="[1103,1151,446,470]" pageId="61" pageNumber="952">type</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingCountry id="B9ABDAD0FFDCBA1CFB11FE0DFB71FE64" box="[1228,1276,446,469]" name="Iraq" pageId="61" pageNumber="952">Iraq</collectingCountry>
, however, was found in Ashar Creek, 
<quantity id="064437A5FFDCBA1CFBF9FE6EFBE5FE44" box="[1060,1128,477,501]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.6" pageId="61" pageNumber="952" unit="km" value="96.0">96 km</quantity>
from the sea, and presumably freshwater (
<bibRefCitation id="A52DE7B1FFDCBA1CFC70FE4EFBC6FDA4" author="Calman" box="[941,1099,509,533]" firstAuthor="Calman" pageId="61" pageNumber="952" pagination="62 - 65" refId="ref68102" refString="Calman WT (1920) A new crab of the genus Sesarma from Basra. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 9, 5 (25): 62 - 65, figs. A, B." type="journal article" year="1920">Calman, 1920</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="89A6C9CBFFDCBA1CFCF0FD8EFBE7FDC4" pageId="61" pageNumber="952" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="C1039A40FFDCBA1CFCF0FD8EFBE7FDC4" blockId="61.[813,1451,573,629]" pageId="61" pageNumber="952">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFDCBA1CFCF0FD8EFC34FDE4" bold="true" box="[813,953,573,597]" pageId="61" pageNumber="952">Distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry id="B9ABDAD0FFDCBA1CFC17FD8DFC78FDE4" box="[970,1013,574,597]" name="Iraq" pageId="61" pageNumber="952">Iraq</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="B9ABDAD0FFDCBA1CFBEDFD8DFBD3FDE4" box="[1072,1118,574,597]" name="Iran" pageId="61" pageNumber="952">Iran</collectingCountry>
, Persian Gulf (
<bibRefCitation id="A52DE7B1FFDCBA1CFAD5FD8EFA2AFDE4" author="Calman" box="[1288,1447,573,597]" firstAuthor="Calman" pageId="61" pageNumber="952" pagination="62 - 65" refId="ref68102" refString="Calman WT (1920) A new crab of the genus Sesarma from Basra. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 9, 5 (25): 62 - 65, figs. A, B." type="journal article" year="1920">Calman, 1920</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="A52DE7B1FFDCBA1CFCF0FDEEFBD3FDC4" author="Naderloo &amp; Schubart" box="[813,1118,605,629]" firstAuthor="Naderloo" pageId="61" pageNumber="952" pagination="61 - 68" refId="ref73102" refString="Naderloo R &amp; Schubart CD (2009) Redescription and mitochondrial identification of Chiromantes boulengeri (Calman, 1920) (Decapoda: Brachyura: Sesarmidae) based on fresh material from the Persian Gulf, Iran. Zootaxa, 2128: 61 - 68." type="journal article" year="2009">Naderloo &amp; Schubart, 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
